    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix XML output formatting in LCS Client Identity dump function\n\n### Summary\nThe `dump_lcs_client_identity_xml()` function was not properly formatting its XML output. The function directly printed the result of `dump_octet_string_xml()` without proper indentation, causing malformed XML structure when debug output was enabled.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/LcsClientIdentity.c`: \n  - Added `#include <string.h>` for string manipulation functions\n  - Refactored `dump_lcs_client_identity_xml()` to properly parse and indent the XML output from `dump_octet_string_xml()`\n  - Added line-by-line processing with proper 4-space indentation to match other XML dump functions in the codebase\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen NAS debug output is enabled (`NAS_DEBUG` defined), the LCS Client Identity IE XML dump would appear malformed:\n```xml\n<Lcs Client Identity>\n    <IEI>0xXX</IEI>\n<Length>X</Length>\n    <values>0xXX 0xXX ...</values>\n</Lcs Client Identity>\n```\n\nThe `<Length>` and `<values>` tags were not properly indented, making the XML structure inconsistent with other IEs. After this fix, the output will be properly formatted with consistent indentation.\n"
}